{"id": "duc04-testb-32:20#60", "contents": "The Justice Department's antitrust suit against Microsoft is a natural progression of previous investigations. The officials involved agree that the antitrust division operates independently of the administration's political considerations. Charles Rule, a former assistant attorney general who headed the antitrust division during the Bush administration, now serves as an adviser and advocate for Microsoft. Rule stated that during his tenure, the White House never interfered with the antitrust division's decisions, and he believes this policy has not changed under the Clinton administration."}
